# This file is intentionally minimal.
#
# All hermes-agent configuration (API keys, tool credentials, messaging tokens)
# lives inside the persistent volume at ~/.hermes/.env, written by
# `./hermes setup`. That keeps state in one place and survives rebuilds.
#
# Only use this file for env vars that genuinely need to be present at container
# boot (before hermes reads ~/.hermes/.env) — e.g. HTTP_PROXY, TZ, debug flags.
#
# Examples (uncomment to use):
# TZ=Europe/Berlin
# HTTP_PROXY=http://proxy.local:3128
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://proxy.local:3128
